-- China Aims to Develop 10 Billion-Dollar Software Firms, Shanghai News Says
-- B y   B l o o m b e r g   N e w s
-- 2010-12-14T00:30:34Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-12-14/china-aims-to-develop-10-billion-dolar-software-firms-shanghai-news-says.html
China plans to have more than 10
software companies each with annual sales exceeding 10 billion
yuan ($1.5 billion) over the next five years, the Shanghai
Securities News reported today, citing Zhao Xiaofan, Vice
Chairman of China Software Industry Association.  The government will not change its policy for supporting the
industry, the newspaper cited Zhao as saying.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
